The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Attari, March 4 (PTI): A Pakistani intruder was shot dead and another arrested in an encounter with the BSF on the Indo-Pak border at Attari yesterday.          
	The intruders had opened fire when BSF troops asked them to surrender. Heroin worth Rs 40 crore was seized from them.                  
	 Chandigarh (PTI): A retired air vice-marshal allegedly committed suicide by shooting himself at his residence on Wednesday. Manjit Singh Dhillon, a highly decorated IAF helicopter pilot who had won several gallantry awards, was suffering from depression, police said. Dhillon, 69, shot himself through the chin. He is survived by his wife, a son and a daughter.                   
	 Chandigarh (PTI): The Punjab Assembly on Wednesday passed a resolution seeking the withdrawal of a ban on turbans in France, and asked the Centre to take up the issue with authorities there. The French government has banned students from wearing turbans to school and college.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Slumdog Millionaire child actors Azharuddin Mohammed Ismail and Rubina Ali will feature in Vasu Bhagnanis upcoming film Kal Kissne Dekha which also marks the debut of his son Jackky. They shot a sequence on Tuesday in which Jack-ky saves them when they are caught in a chaos at the airport after they return from the Oscars.                  
	 Kanpur (PTI): Three persons were arrested on Tuesday for allegedly manufacturing adulterated ghee. Police raided a house and seized 2 quintals of the adulterated product with labels of leading brands. The trio told the police they were to sell the ghee on Holi.                  
	 New Delhi: A fight over a pending electricity bill with the tenant cost the life of a 52-year-old woman on Tuesday. Devi Rani died after she was beaten up allegedly by her tenant Inderjit and his son Rinku at their residence Delhis Geeta Colony. Rani was attacked when she tried to stop the tenants from beating up her son Vijay Kumar, who had asked them to pay the bill.                                                                                                                           
